Execrcise 1: basic examples for runing mace tasks.
1.1 Train a MLIP from scratch
    Note: you can change some parameters in 'submiss.sh' like E0s='average', replace 'valid_frac' to 'valid_file', change 'hiddeirreps', try to understand all important parameters. 
    sbatch submiss.sh 

1.2 Refine a MLIP from a given MLIP
    The initial MLIP could be from anywhere, foundation model or your own model.
    sbatch submiss.sh 
1.3 Optimize structures when given a MLIP
    Check different optimization algorithm, here I used 'BFGS'
    sbatch md_mace.sh

1.4 Implement molecular dynamcis when given a MLIP
    Check different molecular algorithm, here I used 'Langevin'
    sbatch md_mace.sh



Note: visualze trajctories by ASE (interface) 'ase -T gui mace_md_traj.xyz'